        <h2 id="quick-answer" class="mt-4">Quick Answer: TradingView to TradeLocker with AlgoWay</h2>

        <p>To connect TradingView alerts to TradeLocker, prepare your TradeLocker login details, create a TradeLocker webhook in AlgoWay, copy the AlgoWay webhook URL, create a TradingView alert, enable <strong>Webhook URL</strong> in TradingView and send a valid JSON message.</p>

        <p>Minimum setup checklist:</p>

        <ol>
            <li>TradeLocker broker URL or platform URL;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker email;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker password;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker server name from the broker email;</li>
            <li>numeric TradeLocker Account ID;</li>
            <li>AlgoWay webhook with <strong>Source</strong> set to TradingView and <strong>Platform</strong> set to TradeLocker;</li>
            <li>Trade Type selected: Hedge or Reverse;</li>
            <li>TradingView alert with webhook URL enabled;</li>
            <li>valid JSON message for TradeLocker execution.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>After this setup, a TradingView alert can open, close, reverse or manage a TradeLocker order through AlgoWay, depending on the JSON command you send.</p>

        <h2 id="what-this-solves" class="mt-4">What This Setup Solves</h2>

        <p>Many traders use TradingView for strategy logic, Pine Script indicators and alert creation, but their funded account or broker account runs on TradeLocker. The gap is execution. A normal TradingView alert can notify you, but it does not automatically place a TradeLocker order by itself.</p>

        <p>AlgoWay acts as the execution bridge:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>TradingView remains the signal source;</li>
            <li>AlgoWay receives the webhook alert;</li>
            <li>AlgoWay validates the JSON payload;</li>
            <li>AlgoWay applies route settings such as platform, quantity multiplier and trade mode;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker receives the final order command;</li>
            <li>AlgoWay logs the incoming alert and execution response.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>This is useful for automated TradingView strategies, manual TradingView price alerts, Pine Script alert conditions, prop firm TradeLocker accounts, copy-trading routes and traders who want one automation dashboard for TradeLocker plus other platforms.</p>

        <h2 id="tradelocker-tradingview" class="mt-4">TradeLocker TradingView Charts vs TradingView Webhook Automation</h2>

        <p>TradeLocker includes TradingView charting inside its own platform. That is useful for analysis inside TradeLocker, but it is not the same as taking an alert from your separate TradingView account and turning that alert into an automated TradeLocker order.</p>

        <p>This page is about the second case:</p>

        <pre><code>Your TradingView account → webhook alert → AlgoWay → your TradeLocker account</code></pre>

        <p>That distinction matters for SEO and for users. A trader may search “connect TradeLocker to TradingView” and find information about built-in charting. The real automation question is different: <strong>how to send TradingView webhook alerts to TradeLocker for order execution</strong>. AlgoWay handles that route.</p>

        <h2 id="before" class="mt-4">Before You Start</h2>

        <p>Prepare the following before creating the webhook:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>AlgoWay account;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker account from your broker or prop firm;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker platform URL;</li>
            <li>email used for TradeLocker login;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker password;</li>
            <li>server name from the broker email;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker Account ID digits;</li>
            <li>TradingView strategy, indicator or manual alert condition;</li>
            <li>TradingView plan with webhook alert support;</li>
            <li>small test size for the first alert.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
            <strong>Important:</strong> in AlgoWay, the TradeLocker Account ID should be entered as digits only. Do not paste labels, currency symbols or extra text around it.
        </div>

        <h2 id="account-id" class="mt-4">Step 1. Register on TradeLocker and Find Your Account ID</h2>

        <p>Register on the TradeLocker platform through your broker or prop firm. After registration, the broker normally sends an email with the information needed for login:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>email;</li>
            <li>password;</li>
            <li>TradeLocker platform server name.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Log in to the TradeLocker website using those details.</p>

        <img src="https://algoway.trade/static/img/manuals/tv-td-1@2x.png"
             class="article-img"
             loading="lazy"
             alt="TradeLocker platform login screen for TradingView to TradeLocker automation" decoding="async" width="1200" height="675" />

        <p>In the lower-left corner of the TradeLocker platform, click the dollar icon to view the account selector and Account ID.</p>

        <p><strong>Use only the digits of the Account ID in AlgoWay.</strong> If the interface shows text around the number, copy the number only.</p>

        <img src="https://algoway.trade/static/img/manuals/tv-td-2@2x.png"
             class="article-img"
             loading="lazy"
             alt="Find numeric TradeLocker Account ID for AlgoWay webhook setup" decoding="async" width="1200" height="675" />

        <h2 id="create-webhook" class="mt-4">Step 2. Create a TradeLocker Webhook in AlgoWay</h2>

        <p>Log in to AlgoWay and create a webhook route for TradeLocker execution.</p>

        <ol>
            <li>Open <strong>AlgoWay Dashboard</strong>.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Add Webhook</strong>, <strong>Add Trial Webhook</strong> or <strong>Add Main Webhook</strong>.</li>
            <li>Set <strong>Source</strong> to <strong>TradingView</strong>.</li>
            <li>Set <strong>Platform</strong> to <strong>TradeLocker</strong>.</li>
            <li>Choose the quantity multiplier. For direct JSON quantity, use <strong>Absolute</strong> and <code>1</code>.</li>
            <li>Select <strong>Trade Type</strong>: Hedge or Reverse.</li>
            <li>Enter the TradeLocker platform URL.</li>
            <li>Enter the TradeLocker email.</li>
            <li>Enter the TradeLocker password.</li>
            <li>Enter the TradeLocker server name.</li>
            <li>Enter the numeric Account ID.</li>
            <li>Save the webhook.</li>
        </ol>

        <img src="https://algoway.trade/static/img/manuals/tv-td-3@2x.png"
             class="article-img"
             loading="lazy"
             alt="Open AlgoWay dashboard to add a TradeLocker webhook for TradingView alerts" decoding="async" width="1200" height="675" />

        <p>The main TradeLocker fields in AlgoWay are:</p>

        <table class="table table-bordered table-striped mt-3">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Field</th>
                    <th>Example value</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Source</td>
                    <td>TradingView</td>
                    <td>The alert source that sends the webhook.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Platform</td>
                    <td>TradeLocker</td>
                    <td>The destination where the order should be executed.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Quantity Multiplier</td>
                    <td>Absolute → 1</td>
                    <td>Uses the incoming <code>order_contracts</code> value directly.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Trade Type</td>
                    <td>Hedge or Reverse</td>
                    <td>Controls whether opposite signals open separate exposure or reverse the current position.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>URL</td>
                    <td>TradeLocker platform URL</td>
                    <td>Defines the TradeLocker environment connected to the webhook.</td>
